<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Depose" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Depose,</orth> 1) to divest of office, to dethrone: <bibl n="shak. jn 2.372" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 372</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.107" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 107</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.56" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 56</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.144" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 67</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.192.67" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.192.67" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 192</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.192.67" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 192</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 27</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.478" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 478</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.90" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.4.33" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 4, 33</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.2.24" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.41" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 41</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 45</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.162" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.209" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 209</bibl>. Followed by <emph>of</emph>: <cit><quote>that Lepidus of the triumvirate should be --d,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.6.29" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 6, 29</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to declare upon oath, to swear: <cit><quote>I'll d. I had him in mine arms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 198</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>seeing 'twas he that made you to d., your oath is vain,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 2, 26</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) to put under oath, to cause to swear: <cit><quote>d. him in the justice of his cause,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.30" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 30</bibl></cit>.
